<content type="html"><h2>Core update</h2> <ul> <li>Includes all new functionality and bug fixes up to Obsidian Desktop v1.0.</li> <li>Ongoing UI overhaul with an emphasis on making the app more responsive and mobile-friendly.</li> <li>Phone-only: New bottom navigation bar includes forward/back arrows, tab menu, and quick access to your ribbon items.</li> <li>Phone-only: The left ribbon bar has been removed from the left sidebar. It is now accessible as a menu in the navigation bar. Tap to activate your most recent action. Tap and hold to see a list of all ribbon items.</li> <li>Tabs can now be used on both tablets and phones. On phones, tabs can be accessed with the button on the navigation bar.</li> <li>Phone-only: Added haptic feedback for the context menu and pull-down menu.</li> <li>Tablet-only: Some interface elements like menus and popups will now use the desktop version since there's sufficient space on tablets.</li> <li>Long-press links in Live Preview to show context menu.</li> </ul> </content>
